==English==
===Verb===
'''gish'''

# 1. To inflict crumpling, squashing or otherwise messy damage upon, esp. more damage than a '''ding'''.
Ex. My car got gished in the parking lot.
Ex. Too many stray animals are getting gished on the highway.
# 2. (slang) drunk.
Ex. I had some bad screech and got completely gished.

# 3. To talk overly emotionally/enthusiastically about something or someone.
'''gish on''' or
'''gish about'''

The young reviewer gished on about the handsome actor.

